      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Great question! The opportunity cost can indeed be quantified, even though it's a bit of a tricky calculation. GizmoWorks could estimate the potential increase in revenue from the advertising campaign and compare it to the expected increase in profits from the new 3D printer. They'd look at the projected sales growth from the campaign and the additional revenue the new printer could generate over time. By comparing these figures, they could assign a monetary value to the opportunity cost of choosing one option over the other. It's a bit like weighing the benefits of a new toy against the satisfaction of the treats, and figuring out which one would make your little goblin friend happier in the long run.",
